text.section:
The Department may permit a law enforcement agency of the State or a State unit to connect with and use a computer or communication system established by the Department for statewide use including:
a voice communication system;
a data communication system;
a message switching system;
the Maryland Interagency Law Enforcement System (MILES);
the National Crime Information Center (NCIC); and
the National Law Enforcement Telecommunications System (NLETS).
